{"topic": "Articles", "ss": "NewsApiFeeder", "ts": "2025-04-13T13:57:49Z", "url": "http://blog.livedoor.jp/nanjstu/archives/62286465.html", "publishedAt": "2025-04-13T13:57:49Z", "content": ": https://hayabusa9.5ch.net/test/read.cgi/mnewsplus/1744552091/\r\n1: 2025/04/13() 22:48:11.86 ID:upHr0j7C9\r\n1000 2014/11/30() 00:00:00\r\nWBC\r\n3: 2025/04/13() 22:49:01.67 ID:AFpSK/+c0\r\n8: 2025/04/13() 2… [+518 chars]", "title": "【MLB】ドジャース　16失点で野手が登板　佐々木朗希、山本由伸らのモノマネで笑いを誘い観衆を沸かせる", "fullContent": "転載元: https://hayabusa9.5ch.net/test/read.cgi/mnewsplus/1744552091/\n\n1: 冬月記者 ★ 2025/04/13(日) 22:48:11.86 ID:upHr0j7C9\n\nドジャース 球団史上初の本拠で16失点零敗 屈辱的大敗も野手登板のロハスがモノマネ劇場で観衆沸かせる◇ナ・リーグ ドジャース0―16カブス（2025年4月12日 ロサンゼルス）ドジャースは12日（日本時間13日）、本拠でカブスと対戦。佐々木朗希投手（23）が5回4安打1失点と粘りの投球を見せたが、救援陣が崩れ、0―16で大敗した。16点差以上つけられての零敗は1965年以来60年ぶりの屈辱的な敗戦となった。先発した佐々木朗希がメジャー最長となる5回を投げきり、1失点と力投。ただ、打線が援護できずにいると、0―2の7回に2番手・カスペリアスがつかまり5失点。8回にもガルシアが2ランを被弾するなど4失点し0―11までリードを広げられると、ロハスが“野手登板”する展開に。大敗ムードを払拭するように山本由伸やカーショー、佐々木のフォームを真似て笑いを誘ったが、2イニング目の9回に2ランを被弾するなど失点を重ね、大敗を喫した。チームは今季初の零敗を喫し、開幕2戦目から続いていた14試合連続本塁打の記録もストップした。一方、ここまで勝率.563だったカブスは勝率.733だったドジャースに快勝。米データ分析サイト「オプタ」の公式Xは「シーズン10試合以上で勝率.700以上のチームに対するMLB史上最大の完封勝利となった」とのデータを紹介した。ドジャースが16失点以上で零敗を喫するのは球団史上5度目。1965年はレッズに0―18で敗れた。過去4試合の16失点以上の零敗は全て敵地だった。本拠で大量失点しての零敗は2023年6月17日のジャイアンツ戦の0―15がワースト記録で、本拠ではそれを上回る球団史上初の記録的な大敗となった。"}
{"topic": "Articles", "ss": "NewsApiFeeder", "ts": "2025-04-13T07:00:55Z", "url": "https://www.geeky-gadgets.com/transform-your-ipad-these-apps-are-game-changers/", "publishedAt": "2025-04-13T07:00:55Z", "content": "Your iPad is more than just a device for streaming videos or browsing social mediait can be a powerful tool to enhance productivity and organization. With the right apps, you can streamline your work… [+6146 chars]", "title": "Transform Your iPad: These Apps Are Game Changers!", "fullContent": "Your iPad is more than just a device for streaming videos or browsing social media—it can be a powerful tool to enhance productivity and organization. With the right apps, you can streamline your workflow, minimize distractions, and focus on achieving your goals. The video from Dailytekk explores essential iPad apps that cater to various productivity needs, from managing emails to using AI for smarter workflows. These tools are designed to help you stay organized, save time, and tackle everyday challenges with ease.\n\nEmail Management: Take Control of Your Inbox\n\nManaging your inbox can often feel like an endless task, but apps like Hey Email simplify the process. This app helps you filter out spam, prioritize important messages, and organize your emails efficiently. By focusing on what matters most, you can reduce the time spent sifting through irrelevant emails and instead dedicate your attention to meaningful communication. Whether you’re managing work-related correspondence or personal messages, a decluttered inbox can significantly improve your focus and reduce stress. With tools like Hey Email, you can regain control of your inbox and make email management a seamless part of your day.\n\nNote-Taking and Organization: Your Digital Workspace\n\nFor organizing thoughts, projects, and daily tasks, Craft stands out as a versatile app. It allows you to create structured documents, manage notes, and plan long-term projects with ease. Its intuitive interface and seamless syncing across devices ensure that your ideas are always accessible, whether you’re at home or on the go. From drafting reports to brainstorming creative projects, Craft provides a centralized workspace that keeps you organized and productive. By integrating this app into your routine, you can simplify complex tasks and maintain a clear overview of your priorities.\n\nWeb Browsing with AI: Smarter, Faster Research\n\nOnline research can be time-consuming, but AI-enhanced browsers like Arc Browser make the process more efficient. This app offers features such as article summarization, advanced search capabilities, and idea generation, allowing you to find and process information quickly. Whether you’re conducting in-depth research for work or seeking inspiration for personal projects, Arc Browser helps you save time while delivering valuable insights. By incorporating AI into your browsing experience, you can streamline your research efforts and focus on applying the information effectively.\n\nContent Storage: Simplify Digital Organization\n\nKeeping track of digital content can be challenging, especially when juggling multiple tasks. MyMind offers a hands-off solution by acting as a digital “junk drawer” for your ideas, articles, and images. Unlike traditional organization tools, this app uses AI to surface relevant content when you need it, eliminating the need for manual sorting. Whether you’re saving inspiration for a project or archiving important information, MyMind ensures that nothing gets lost. For busy individuals, this app provides a stress-free way to manage digital clutter and maintain focus on what matters most.\n\nHandwritten Notes Integration: Bridging Analog and Digital\n\nIf you prefer the tactile experience of handwritten notes but need the convenience of digital access, the Remarkable App is an ideal solution. This app syncs handwritten notes from the Remarkable tablet to your iPad, allowing you to combine the benefits of both analog and digital tools. Whether you’re brainstorming ideas, reviewing meeting notes, or sketching concepts, Remarkable App ensures that your handwritten thoughts are always accessible. By bridging the gap between paper and digital, this app enhances your ability to capture and organize ideas effectively.\n\nVoice-to-Text Transcription: Capture Ideas on the Go\n\nSuper Whisper is an invaluable tool for capturing ideas quickly and accurately. This app converts spoken words into text with remarkable precision, making it easy to record meetings, draft content, or jot down thoughts while on the move. By integrating voice-to-text transcription into your workflow, you can ensure that no valuable insights are lost, even during busy moments. Super Whisper not only saves time but also enhances your ability to document and act on ideas efficiently.\n\nShortcut Management: Streamline Repetitive Tasks\n\nRepetitive tasks can consume valuable time and energy, but apps like OneTap simplify these processes. This app allows you to manage frequently used text-based shortcuts, such as AI prompts or canned responses, with a single tap. By reducing the need to switch between tools or retype information, OneTap helps you maintain focus and efficiency throughout your day. Whether you’re responding to emails or automating routine tasks, this app ensures that repetitive actions no longer disrupt your workflow.\n\nAI Tools for Productivity: Brainstorm and Problem-Solve\n\nAI-powered apps like ChatGPT and Grock offer creative and analytical support for a variety of tasks. These tools can help you brainstorm ideas, analyze data, and solve complex problems with minimal effort. Whether you’re working on a professional project or exploring new concepts, these apps provide valuable insights and assistance. By incorporating AI into your productivity toolkit, you can tackle challenges more effectively and unlock new opportunities for growth.\n\nKey Takeaways for Maximizing iPad Productivity\n\nBy integrating these essential iPad apps into your daily routine, you can transform your device into a productivity powerhouse. Each app addresses specific challenges, from managing emails and organizing notes to using AI for smarter workflows. With tools like Hey Email, Craft, and Arc Browser, you can save time, stay organized, and focus on what truly matters. Whether you’re managing personal tasks or professional responsibilities, these apps empower you to achieve your goals with greater efficiency and ease.\n\nMaster iPad productivity apps with the help of our in-depth articles and helpful guides.\n\nSource & Image Credit: Dailytekk\n\n\n\nLatest Geeky Gadgets Deals\n\nSome of our articles include affiliate links. If you buy something through one of these links, Geeky Gadgets may earn an affiliate commission. Learn about our Disclosure Policy"}
{"topic": "Articles", "ss": "NewsApiFeeder", "ts": "2025-04-13T19:00:24Z", "url": "https://www.brothers-brick.com/2025/04/13/a-lego-lair-for-new-orleans-blood-suckers/", "publishedAt": "2025-04-13T19:00:24Z", "content": "Jeff Chapman has carved out a place in the LEGO builder scene with a bloody knife, specializing in  the macabre with a historical twist. While most of his creations so far have centered around Salem,… [+2482 chars]", "title": "Join our haunted tour of this epic LEGO lair for New Orleans vampires", "fullContent": "Jeff Chapman has carved out a place in the LEGO builder scene with a bloody knife, specializing in the macabre with a historical twist. While most of his creations so far have centered around Salem, for his latest build, Jeff travels south to New Orleans, another American city brimming with haunted history. Like his New England builds, Jeff bases his model on a real-world location, in this case an iconic corner building on Royal Street that was home to the legendary Jacques St Germain, the French Quarter vampire!\n\nJeff’s models are always best experienced via narrated tour of history and build process on his Spooky Brixx YouTube channel, which you can watch here. Or skip down to a photo gallery for more pics of this haunted masterpiece.\n\nIn past builds, Jeff has stuck to exteriors only because those buildings had few and tiny windows, often obscured by stained glass lighting effects. As the Vampire house has so many windows (a bit ironic!), this time Jeff included a few vignettes that are visibile behind “glass,” such as this gallery. Jeff focused on interior vignettes Thst can be best appreciated through the windows, as his models aren’t designed to come apart like modulars. This view also gives a peek at how the arches over the larger windows were constructed by clipping onto a bent bar. Under each stack of window pannels, Jeff adds a crate for extra texture.\n\nThe building’s backside is less ornate but doesn’t skimp on textured brickwork. Plenty of spooky accessories set the mood for blood-sucking debauchery.\n\nA higher angle is helpful for appreciating the distinctive wide balacony associated with the district. The roof is made from an enviable number of roof tiles and a smattering of bats.\n\nRunning along the balony is Count Jacques himself, chasing a would-be victim. According to local legend, a woman threw herself from the balcony and was found with bite marks in her neck. Police searched the building and found bottles of blood but Jacques St. Germain had disappeared! From this vantage we can also appreciate the lovely iron railing\n\nAt street level, a visiting Orlock-inspired guest drops by. As always, Jeff kills it with the atmospheric lighting.\n\nPeeking through this window we can glimpse another vampire enjoying a releaxing bath. Perhaps it’s Elizabeth Bathory, here to try out the local beignets and blood.\n\nJeff teases that this is but the first of hopefully many French Quarter builds. Can we expect a LEGO Marie Laveau in our future?\n\nRelated"}
{"topic": "Articles", "ss": "NewsApiFeeder", "ts": "2025-04-13T17:27:00Z", "url": "https://anfieldindex.com/80967/david-lynchs-5-key-takeaways-from-liverpools-2-1-win-over-west-ham.html", "publishedAt": "2025-04-13T17:27:00Z", "content": "In the latest post-match breakdown from Anfield, Liverpool reporter David Lynch dissected the Reds’ narrow but crucial 2-1 victory over West Ham. Speaking on his podcast-style reaction from the press… [+3207 chars]", "title": "David Lynch’s 5 Key Takeaways from Liverpool’s 2-1 Win Over West Ham", "fullContent": "David Lynch’s 5 Key Takeaways from Liverpool’s 2-1 Win Over West Ham\n\nIn the latest post-match breakdown from Anfield, Liverpool reporter David Lynch dissected the Reds’ narrow but crucial 2-1 victory over West Ham. Speaking on his podcast-style reaction from the press box, Lynch offered sharp insight into what this win means for Liverpool’s title charge, who shone under pressure, and where improvements are still needed. Here are his five key takeaways from a game that kept fans on the edge of their seats.\n\nFirst-Half Control Showed Liverpool’s Quality\n\nLynch was impressed with the Reds’ opening half, stating, “I think the first half… was one of the best they’ve played for a while really. I thought they were popping it around, they looked really dangerous.” With Luis Díaz opening the scoring, it seemed Liverpool might enjoy a more comfortable afternoon. The stats backed up the dominance: “Liverpool chalked up 1.26 expected goals in that first half, and West Ham just 0.36.”\n\nAtmosphere and Jeopardy Go Hand in Hand\n\nWhile the first half performance was assertive, Lynch acknowledged a significant dip after the break: “Liverpool not anywhere close to the first half level of performance… couldn’t get the second goal, didn’t really threaten.” However, he observed how the late drama reinvigorated both crowd and players: “Once the equaliser goes in, it kind of changes things… Anfield absolutely ramped up from that moment.”\n\nThat electricity culminated in Virgil van Dijk’s towering 89th-minute header, about which Lynch said, “He rises highest to nod that one in and the place absolutely erupts.”\n\nAlisson Becker and Alexis Mac Allister Stand Tall\n\nDespite Van Dijk’s headline-grabbing winner, Lynch made a point to praise Alisson Becker: “Liverpool would not win the game today if it weren’t for some of the saves he pulls out in the most difficult moments.”\n\nIn midfield, Alexis Mac Allister’s contribution was immense. Lynch was glowing: “I just think he’s Liverpool’s best midfielder for me and he has been all season… a world-class player really.” Citing his six ground duels won, four shots, and two chances created—including the match-winning corner—Lynch underlined Mac Allister’s complete performance: “A big, big clutch moment he delivers in.”\n\nArne Slot’s Substitutions Didn’t Hit the Mark\n\nIn a rare critique of Arne Slot, Lynch reflected on the tactical changes that nearly derailed Liverpool’s rhythm. “One of the rare games this season where Slot’s subs haven’t quite worked for him,” he noted, singling out the decision to replace Conor Bradley with Jarell Quansah at right-back.\n\nHe explained: “Quansah… absolutely emptied it to no one under zero pressure. It just shows you, Conor Bradley would have kept possession.” Lynch concluded, “That one put Liverpool under pressure when they didn’t need to be.”\n\nCharacter Over Style as Liverpool Close in on the Title\n\nWhile some may criticise Liverpool’s second-half stumbles, Lynch offered perspective: “At this point of the season, it’s all about just getting over the line.” With the Reds now “13 points clear,” he urged fans to savour the moment, even if performances aren’t always fluent.\n\n“If you want to accuse Liverpool of limping over the line… just think that there are 19 other teams who absolutely wish they were in Liverpool’s position.”\n\nAs the final whistle blew, the message was clear: results matter most in the business end of a title race, and Liverpool, led by Slot, have both the talent and tenacity to finish the job."}
