{"topic": "Articles", "ss": "NewsApiFeeder", "ts": "2025-04-13T15:00:01Z", "url": "https://www.geeky-gadgets.com/improved-nighttime-viewing-enable-ultra-dark-mode-on-iphone-today/", "publishedAt": "2025-04-13T15:00:01Z", "content": "Apple’s latest iOS update introduces a noteworthy enhancement to its dark mode functionality: the ultra dark mode for iPhone. This feature is designed to provide deeper customization, improved access… [+4854 chars]", "title": "Improved Nighttime Viewing: Enable ULTRA Dark Mode on iPhone Today", "fullContent": "Apple’s latest iOS update introduces a noteworthy enhancement to its dark mode functionality: the ultra dark mode for iPhone. This feature is designed to provide deeper customization, improved accessibility, and a more immersive experience for low-light environments. Whether you’re looking to reduce eye strain or personalize your device, ultra dark mode offers a significant upgrade to the iPhone’s user interface. The video below from iDeviceHelp gives us more details on the ultra dark mode.\n\nWhat Makes Ultra Dark Mode Unique?\n\nUltra dark mode builds upon the existing dark mode by introducing advanced features and customization options. These updates are tailored to meet both aesthetic preferences and practical needs, making sure a seamless and user-friendly experience for all users.\n\nSystem-Wide Dark Interface: Ultra dark mode extends the dark theme across all system applications, such as Settings, Calendar, and Messages. This creates a consistent, darker interface that enhances usability in dimly lit environments.\n\nUltra dark mode extends the dark theme across all system applications, such as Settings, Calendar, and Messages. This creates a consistent, darker interface that enhances usability in dimly lit environments. Enhanced Accessibility: A new “Reduce White Point” feature allows users to dim the brightest elements of their display. Adjustable between 60-70%, this setting is particularly beneficial for reducing eye strain during nighttime use.\n\nA new “Reduce White Point” feature allows users to dim the brightest elements of their display. Adjustable between 60-70%, this setting is particularly beneficial for reducing eye strain during nighttime use. Home Screen Customization: Users can now personalize their home screens with dark or tinted icons and darker-toned wallpapers. This creates a cohesive and visually appealing ultra dark mode aesthetic that complements the overall interface.\n\nUsers can now personalize their home screens with dark or tinted icons and darker-toned wallpapers. This creates a cohesive and visually appealing ultra dark mode aesthetic that complements the overall interface. Dynamic Adaptation: Ultra dark mode can adapt to ambient lighting conditions, automatically adjusting brightness and contrast levels to suit the environment. This ensures optimal visibility and comfort at all times.\n\nHow to Activate and Control Ultra Dark Mode\n\nApple has simplified the process of allowing and managing ultra dark mode, offering multiple control options for added convenience. These intuitive methods make it easy for users to switch modes and customize their experience.\n\nControl Center Access: A dedicated toggle for “Reduce White Point” can be added to the Control Center, allowing quick and easy adjustments to brightness levels.\n\nA dedicated toggle for “Reduce White Point” can be added to the Control Center, allowing quick and easy adjustments to brightness levels. Lock Screen Activation: Ultra dark mode can be enabled or disabled directly from the lock screen, providing a fast and convenient way to switch modes as needed.\n\nUltra dark mode can be enabled or disabled directly from the lock screen, providing a fast and convenient way to switch modes as needed. Action Button Customization: On select iPhone models, the action button can now be configured to activate ultra dark mode. This feature is particularly useful for users who frequently alternate between light and dark modes.\n\nOn select iPhone models, the action button can now be configured to activate ultra dark mode. This feature is particularly useful for users who frequently alternate between light and dark modes. Scheduled Activation: Users can schedule ultra dark mode to activate automatically at specific times, such as during evening hours. This ensures a seamless transition to a darker interface when it’s most needed.\n\nWhy Ultra Dark Mode Matters\n\nUltra dark mode is more than just a visual enhancement—it offers practical benefits that significantly improve the overall user experience. By addressing both functional and aesthetic needs, this feature appeals to a wide range of users and use cases.\n\nMinimized Eye Strain: The darker interface, combined with adjustable white point settings, makes it easier to use your device in low-light conditions. This reduces discomfort and fatigue, especially during prolonged use.\n\nThe darker interface, combined with adjustable white point settings, makes it easier to use your device in low-light conditions. This reduces discomfort and fatigue, especially during prolonged use. Greater Personalization: With options for dark-themed icons, wallpapers, and interface elements, you can customize your device to align with your preferences while maintaining a cohesive and polished look.\n\nWith options for dark-themed icons, wallpapers, and interface elements, you can customize your device to align with your preferences while maintaining a cohesive and polished look. Improved Accessibility: Features like “Reduce White Point” and dynamic adaptation ensure that users with visual sensitivities can comfortably navigate their devices without straining their eyes.\n\nFeatures like “Reduce White Point” and dynamic adaptation ensure that users with visual sensitivities can comfortably navigate their devices without straining their eyes. Energy Efficiency: On devices with OLED displays, ultra dark mode can help conserve battery life by reducing the power consumption of darker pixels. This makes it a practical choice for users who prioritize battery longevity.\n\nThe Practical Benefits of Ultra Dark Mode\n\nUltra dark mode represents a thoughtful evolution in iPhone customization and accessibility. By combining system-wide dark interface adjustments, enhanced control options, and a focus on reducing eye strain, Apple has created a feature that is both practical and visually appealing. Whether you’re using your device during the day or at night, ultra dark mode offers a tailored, immersive experience that adapts to your needs. Its ability to balance functionality with personalization ensures that it remains a valuable tool for a wide range of users, enhancing both usability and comfort.\n\nExpand your understanding of dark mode with additional resources from our extensive library of articles.\n\nSource & Image Credit: iDeviceHelp\n\n\n\nLatest Geeky Gadgets Deals\n\nSome of our articles include affiliate links. If you buy something through one of these links, Geeky Gadgets may earn an affiliate commission. Learn about our Disclosure Policy"}
{"topic": "Articles", "ss": "NewsApiFeeder", "ts": "2025-04-13T12:49:06Z", "url": "https://www.globalresearch.ca/reflections-vietnam-british-empire-holy-week-bo-yin-ra/5884324", "publishedAt": "2025-04-13T12:49:06Z", "content": "Vietnam \r\nA good friend is traveling through Southeast Asia and is presently on a motorcycle tour through Vietnam. This is a place the US tried to obliterate from the planet half a century ago but fa… [+7566 chars]", "title": "Reflections on Vietnam, British Empire, Holy Week, Bô Yin Râ. Richard C. Cook", "fullContent": "Vietnam\n\nA good friend is traveling through Southeast Asia and is presently on a motorcycle tour through Vietnam. This is a place the US tried to obliterate from the planet half a century ago but failed, thank God. I personally declined to participate, as did many young men of my generation. In retaliation, the CIA tried to kill us with LSD, thorazine, and other poisons. Some survived, some were crippled, many didn’t make it. Come to think of it, wasn’t this what the ongoing COVID “planscamdemic” has been all about?\n\nHere’s a nice pic of a couple of happy Vietnamese boys whose country prevailed despite the genocide. Maybe we’ll see pics like this of Palestinian boys someday. Do you think?\n\n.\n\nSource\n\n.\n\nBritish Empire\n\nI have been reading biographies of our Founding Fathers. I have finished ones on George Washington, Alexander Hamilton, and am now reading one on John Adams. One reason Adams reaches out to me is that like him, I also have ancestors (two and possibly three lines) that go back to the 1630s and the Great Puritan Migration. In fact, like Adams forebears, they also settled in and around Braintree, Massachusetts, so must have known each other.\n\nAdams writes in his notes while serving as post-revolution emissary to England, that there were plenty there who would just have soon annihilated the US from the globe as granted us independence. Like we tried to do to Vietnam. The hatred ran that deep. When that didn’t work, these people yet assumed that sooner or later the Americans would return to the British fold. Adams wrote:\n\n“There is a strong propensity in this people to believe that America is weary of her independence; that she wishes to come back; that the states are in confusion; Congress has lost its authority; no laws, no order, poverty, distress, ruin, and wretchedness; … that smuggling will defeat all our prohibitions, imposts, and revenues…This they love to believe.”\n\nSo it seems pertinent that I will soon be continuing my serialization of my book Our Country, Then and Now with Chapter 8, entitled “Rule Britannia.” This chapter traces how the British Empire began its march to world domination in the late 16th century during the reign of Elizabeth I, Britain’s constant warfare against European powers over the next several centuries, the crushing defeat of France during the Napoleonic Wars, the consolidation of British hegemony during the 19th century, and the epochal struggle over South African gold and diamonds culminating with the Boer Wars. I conclude with the campaign by Cecil Rhodes and Nathaniel Rothschild to form a “secret society” with the goal to “recover America for the British Empire.” (Rhodes’s words)\n\nWhat I am trying to do is figure out how Britain was able to sucker the US into providing the money and manpower for them to annihilate Germany during World Wars I and II and to see clearly how they are doing it today to get the US to fight World War III against Russia. This includes joining with Israel in keeping the US fully bogged down in the Islamic world with the “War on Terror,” which I see as just another British imperial project.\n\nHoly Week\n\nTomorrow is Palm Sunday, which commemorates Jesus’s final entry into Jerusalem. Maundy Thursday is the day of Jesus’s Last Supper with his disciples, and Good Friday is the Crucifixion. Then comes Easter Sunday, April 20, the day of the Resurrection.\n\nThis year both the Eastern and Western churches celebrate Easter on the same day, which is a rarity due to the difference in calendars. A good omen for sure! Some have commented that the divide between Russia and the rest of Europe reflects the 11th century schism between the Orthodox and Catholic religions. If so, it’s time for healing!\n\nLately we have been posting regular readings from Jesus’s journey toward his Passion, mainly from the Gospel of John. Even though these don’t get as may “hits” as our political articles, they still have been getting a lot of “reads,” “likes,” and comments.\n\nWe certainly don’t mean any of this to imply an endorsement of any particular denomination or even the Christian religion over any other faith. We do happen to believe that Jesus was a real person and that what he suffered and accomplished has application to every persuasion and every individual. Through him we are seeing spiritual principles unfold and demonstrated in the most vivid and often painful way.\n\nWe would also very much like to see countries, like the US, that profess to have some degree of respect for religion actually live up to that by giving up their evil and sinful ways, particularly the greed and violence that seems to rule the world today. A word to our leaders: stop making excuses.\n\nBô Yin Râ\n\nImage is from the Public Domain\n\nWe have greatly appreciated the positive responses to our choice to focus on the spiritual writings of German spiritual master Bô Yin Râ (Joseph Anton Schneiderfranken (1876-1943). He doesn’t write only about Jesus and the Christian religion, as he often focuses more on broad spiritual principles and practices. Still, his commentaries on Jesus himself are priceless in terms of explaining and clearing up a lot of the confusion that reigns in our attitudes toward Christianity.\n\nAccordingly, we will be pleased during Holy Week to present a series of six successive postings about Jesus and his mission by Bô Yin Râ that will run from Monday through Thursday, then on Saturday and Sunday. Friday will be devoted to a posting on the Catholic ceremony of the Stations of the Cross, along with some musical selections.\n\nConclusion\n\nEven with so much going on in the world, you will certainly excuse us for taking a break from most news-related postings during the coming week.\n\nAs always, we are grateful to our growing number of readers for sticking with us and taking part in our very humble mission.\n\nFadi, Lewis, and I wish you, your friends, your families, your colleagues, and all with whose lives you are linked a wonderful springtime and a happy and blessed Easter.\n\n*\n\nClick the share button below to email/forward this article. Follow us on Instagram and X and subscribe to our Telegram Channel. Feel free to repost Global Research articles with proper attribution.\n\nThis article was originally published on Three Sages.\n\nRichard C. Cook is a retired U.S. federal analyst with extensive experience across various government agencies, including the U.S. Civil Service Commission, FDA, the Carter White House, NASA, and the U.S. Treasury. He is a graduate of the College of William and Mary. As a whistleblower at the time of the Challenger disaster, he exposed the flawed O-ring joints that destroyed the Space Shuttle, documenting his story in the book “Challenger Revealed.” After serving at Treasury, he became a vocal critic of the private finance-controlled monetary system, detailing his concerns in “We Hold These Truths: The Hope of Monetary Reform.” He served as an adviser to the American Monetary Institute and worked with Congressman Dennis Kucinich to advocate for replacing the Federal Reserve with a genuine national currency. See his new book, Our Country, Then and Now, Clarity Press, 2023. Also see his Three Sages Substack and his American Geopolitical Institute articles at https://www.vtforeignpolicy.com/category/agi/.\n\n“Every human enterprise must serve life, must seek to enrich existence on earth, lest man become enslaved where he seeks to establish his dominion!” Bô Yin Râ (Joseph Anton Schneiderfranken, 1876-1943), translation by Posthumus Projects Amsterdam, 2014. Also download the Kober Press edition of The Book on the Living God here.\n\nGlobal Research is a reader-funded media. We do not accept any funding from corporations or governments. Help us stay afloat. Click the image below to make a one-time or recurring donation."}
{"topic": "Articles", "ss": "NewsApiFeeder", "ts": "2025-04-13T06:02:25Z", "url": "https://www.geeky-gadgets.com/multiple-emails-one-gmail-account/", "publishedAt": "2025-04-13T06:02:25Z", "content": "In a world where digital communication is central to personal and professional life, managing multiple email addresses efficiently has become a critical skill. Gmail, with its comprehensive features,… [+6268 chars]", "title": "How To Create Multiple Email Addresses In One Gmail Account (2025)", "fullContent": "In a world where digital communication is central to personal and professional life, managing multiple email addresses efficiently has become a critical skill. Gmail, with its comprehensive features, offers a solution by allowing you to consolidate multiple email accounts into a single interface. This guide by Manizha & Ryan provides a detailed walkthrough on how to link and manage multiple email addresses within one Gmail account, helping you stay organized, productive, and in control of your communication.\n\nMultiple Emails : One Gmail Account\n\nTL;DR Key Takeaways : Gmail allows you to link multiple email addresses, allowing seamless management of emails from various accounts within a single interface.\n\nCustomizable reply settings let you respond from the appropriate email address, making sure professional and context-appropriate communication.\n\nOrganizational tools like labels, filters, and categorized inbox sections help maintain a clutter-free and efficient email workflow.\n\nConsolidating email accounts in Gmail boosts productivity by streamlining workflows, reducing platform switching, and minimizing missed messages.\n\nAdvanced features such as account delegation, custom domains, and search filters provide additional flexibility and control for effective email management.\n\nStep 1: Access Gmail Settings\n\nThe first step in managing multiple email addresses is to access Gmail’s settings. This is where you can configure and customize your account to handle multiple addresses seamlessly. Follow these steps to get started:\n\nClick the gear icon located in the top-right corner of your Gmail inbox.\n\nSelect “See All Settings” from the dropdown menu.\n\nfrom the dropdown menu. Navigate to the “Accounts and Import” tab.\n\nThis section serves as your control panel for linking additional accounts, customizing reply settings, and managing authentication details. Taking the time to familiarize yourself with these options is essential for effective email management.\n\nStep 2: Link Additional Email Addresses\n\nGmail allows you to link multiple email addresses, allowing you to send and receive messages from various accounts without the need to switch platforms. This feature is particularly useful for professionals, students, or anyone managing multiple roles. Here’s how to link an additional email address:\n\nIn the “Accounts and Import” tab, click “Add another email address” .\n\ntab, click . Enter the email address you wish to link and configure the sender name.\n\nSet a reply-to address if needed to ensure responses are directed appropriately.\n\nProvide authentication details, such as SMTP server information, to establish secure communication.\n\nOnce linked, Gmail integrates all your accounts into a unified interface, allowing you to manage emails from different addresses in one place. This not only saves time but also reduces the complexity of juggling multiple platforms.\n\nHow To Create Multiple Email Addresses In One Gmail Account\n\nHere are more guides from our previous articles and guides related to Gmail email management that you may find helpful.\n\nStep 3: Customize Reply Settings\n\nOne of Gmail’s standout features is its ability to customize how you reply to emails. This ensures that your communication remains professional and context-appropriate. Gmail offers two primary options for reply settings:\n\nReply from your default email address, which is ideal for general communication.\n\nReply using the email address to which the message was sent, maintaining consistency and professionalism in specific contexts.\n\nFor example, if you receive a work-related email on a linked professional address, Gmail can automatically reply from that same address. This feature eliminates the risk of confusion and ensures that your responses align with the context of the conversation.\n\nStep 4: Organize Your Inbox\n\nManaging multiple email addresses can quickly become overwhelming without proper organization. Gmail offers several tools to help you maintain a well-structured inbox:\n\nEnable categorized sections such as “Work,” “Personal,” or “University” by navigating to the “Inbox” tab in settings.\n\nor by navigating to the tab in settings. Assign emails to specific categories based on their sender or content to streamline your workflow.\n\nUse labels and filters to automatically sort incoming messages into designated folders.\n\nThese organizational tools make it easier to locate important messages, reduce clutter, and maintain a clear overview of your inbox. By implementing these strategies, you can focus on your priorities without being distracted by unnecessary emails.\n\nStep 5: Maximize Productivity\n\nConsolidating multiple email accounts into one Gmail interface is a powerful way to enhance productivity. By managing all your emails in a single location, you eliminate the need to switch between platforms, which can be time-consuming and inefficient. This approach offers several key benefits:\n\nTime-saving: Streamline your workflow by accessing all emails in one place.\n\nStreamline your workflow by accessing all emails in one place. Improved focus: Reduce the risk of missing important messages by centralizing communication.\n\nReduce the risk of missing important messages by centralizing communication. Enhanced organization: Stay on top of personal, professional, and academic correspondence with ease.\n\nBy using Gmail’s features, you can simplify your email management process and dedicate more time to tasks that truly matter.\n\nAdditional Features to Explore\n\nGmail provides several advanced features that can further enhance your ability to manage multiple email addresses effectively. These tools offer additional flexibility and control:\n\nDelegate Account Access: Grant trusted individuals, such as an assistant or team member, access to your account without sharing your password. This is particularly useful in collaborative environments.\n\nGrant trusted individuals, such as an assistant or team member, access to your account without sharing your password. This is particularly useful in collaborative environments. Custom Domains: Use personalized email addresses (e.g., yourname@yourdomain.com) while benefiting from Gmail’s powerful interface and tools.\n\nUse personalized email addresses (e.g., yourname@yourdomain.com) while benefiting from Gmail’s powerful interface and tools. Search Filters: Use Gmail’s advanced search operators to quickly locate specific emails, even in large and complex inboxes.\n\nThese features allow you to tailor Gmail to your specific needs, making it a versatile tool for managing both personal and professional communication.\n\nStreamline Your Email Management\n\nManaging multiple email addresses within a single Gmail account is a practical and efficient way to simplify your communication. By linking accounts, customizing reply settings, and organizing your inbox, you can stay on top of your responsibilities with minimal effort. Gmail’s advanced features, such as account delegation and custom domains, further enhance its functionality, making it a powerful tool for users with diverse needs.\n\nWhether you’re a busy professional, a student, or someone balancing multiple roles, Gmail’s tools and features ensure that your email management remains stress-free, organized, and productive.\n\nMedia Credit: Tutorials by Manizha & Ryan\n\n\n\nLatest Geeky Gadgets Deals\n\nSome of our articles include affiliate links. If you buy something through one of these links, Geeky Gadgets may earn an affiliate commission. Learn about our Disclosure Policy"}
{"topic": "Articles", "ss": "NewsApiFeeder", "ts": "2025-04-13T09:00:13Z", "url": "https://www.geeky-gadgets.com/apple-watch-ultra-3-major-upgrades/", "publishedAt": "2025-04-13T09:00:13Z", "content": "The Apple Watch Ultra 3, anticipated for release in 2025, is poised to represent a significant evolution in wearable technology. With speculation surrounding a more refined design, advanced connectiv… [+5741 chars]", "title": "Apple Watch Ultra 3: Could These Be the 5 Major Upgrades?", "fullContent": "The Apple Watch Ultra 3, anticipated for release in 2025, is poised to represent a significant evolution in wearable technology. With speculation surrounding a more refined design, advanced connectivity options, and enhanced display capabilities, this next-generation smartwatch could set new benchmarks for functionality and innovation. Below, we explore five potential upgrades that could shape the future of the Apple Watch Ultra series and elevate the wearable experience. The video below from Demon’s Tech gives us more details about the rumored Apple Watch Ultra 3.\n\nA Slimmer, More Compact Design\n\nA major focus of the Apple Watch Ultra 3 appears to be its design. Reports suggest that the device could be up to 15% thinner than its predecessor, offering a sleeker and more compact profile. This reduction in thickness would not only enhance its aesthetic appeal but also improve comfort during extended wear.\n\nThe Ultra series is known for its rugged durability, and the Ultra 3 is expected to maintain this hallmark feature while introducing a more refined form factor. This balance between toughness and elegance could make it an ideal choice for users who demand both functionality and style. Whether you’re navigating extreme outdoor conditions or attending formal events, the slimmer design could make the Ultra 3 a versatile and practical companion.\n\nEnhanced Display: LTPO OLED 3.0 and Brighter Visibility\n\nThe display of the Apple Watch Ultra 3 is rumored to receive a substantial upgrade with the introduction of LTPO OLED 3.0 technology. This advanced display panel could offer improved energy efficiency, smoother transitions between refresh rates, and superior viewing angles. Additionally, the brightness level might increase from 3,000 nits to an impressive 3,500 nits, making sure excellent visibility even in challenging lighting conditions such as direct sunlight or underwater environments.\n\nAn edge-to-edge design could further expand the screen’s usable area, providing a more immersive viewing experience. These enhancements would be particularly beneficial for outdoor enthusiasts, divers, and athletes who rely on clear visuals to monitor metrics or navigate their surroundings. The combination of advanced display technology and increased brightness could make the Ultra 3 a standout device for users who prioritize clarity and functionality.\n\nSatellite Connectivity: Emergency SOS Support\n\nOne of the most intriguing potential features of the Apple Watch Ultra 3 is the addition of satellite connectivity. This capability could enable emergency SOS communication in areas without cellular coverage, allowing users to send distress signals and contact emergency services when off the grid.\n\nFor adventurers, hikers, and campers exploring remote locations, this feature could provide an invaluable safety net. By integrating satellite technology, Apple could position the Ultra 3 as a leader in safety-focused wearables, offering users peace of mind in unpredictable or hazardous situations. This innovation would underscore the Ultra series’ commitment to supporting active lifestyles and enhancing user safety.\n\n5G Connectivity: Faster Speeds and Standalone Functionality\n\nThe Apple Watch Ultra 3 is expected to be the first in its series to incorporate 5G connectivity. This upgrade could deliver faster data speeds, smoother streaming, and more reliable call handling, all powered by eSIM technology. With 5G, users might experience seamless video calls, real-time navigation, and fitness tracking, even in areas with high network demand.\n\nThis advancement aligns with Apple’s broader vision of making the Apple Watch a fully standalone device, reducing its reliance on a paired iPhone. For users seeking greater independence and enhanced functionality, 5G connectivity could represent a significant leap forward. The ability to access high-speed internet and advanced features directly from the watch could redefine how users interact with wearable technology.\n\nRelease Timeline and Pricing Expectations\n\nThe Apple Watch Ultra 3 is likely to be unveiled in September 2025, with availability expected shortly thereafter. While the current model starts at $799, the new version could see a slight price increase due to its advanced features and potential external factors such as inflation or supply chain challenges. However, Apple may also choose to maintain the existing price point to remain competitive in the premium smartwatch market.\n\nThe pricing strategy will likely reflect Apple’s commitment to delivering value while staying ahead of competitors. Whether the price remains consistent or increases slightly, the Ultra 3’s anticipated features could justify its position as a premium wearable device.\n\nAnticipating the Next Leap in Wearable Technology\n\nThe Apple Watch Ultra 3 is shaping up to be a highly anticipated device, blending a sleeker design, innovative display technology, and advanced connectivity features. From its brighter LTPO OLED 3.0 display to the potential inclusion of satellite SOS capabilities and 5G connectivity, the Ultra 3 could offer a compelling mix of innovation and practicality.\n\nFor outdoor enthusiasts, professionals, and tech-savvy users alike, the Ultra 3’s rumored upgrades could redefine expectations for what a smartwatch can achieve. As the release date approaches, these potential advancements highlight Apple’s ongoing commitment to pushing the boundaries of wearable technology and delivering devices that cater to diverse user needs.\n\nHere are more guides from our previous articles and guides related to Apple Watch Ultra 3 that you may find helpful.\n\nSource & Image Credit: Demon’s Tech\n\n\n\nLatest Geeky Gadgets Deals\n\nSome of our articles include affiliate links. If you buy something through one of these links, Geeky Gadgets may earn an affiliate commission. Learn about our Disclosure Policy"}
{"topic": "Articles", "ss": "NewsApiFeeder", "ts": "2025-04-13T13:00:55Z", "url": "https://soranews24.com/2025/04/13/japans-submerged-forest-gets-even-more-beautiful-with-lake-shirakawa-spring-light-up-event%e3%80%90pics%e3%80%91/", "publishedAt": "2025-04-13T13:00:55Z", "content": "When the snow melts, something breathtaking happens at this lake in northern Japan.\r\nDespite offering some of Japans most beautiful scenery, Shirakawa-ko isnt all that famous. Wait a second, you migh… [+2451 chars]", "title": "Japan’s submerged forest gets even more beautiful with Lake Shirakawa spring light-up event【Pics】", "fullContent": "When the snow melts, something breathtaking happens at this lake in northern Japan.\n\nDespite offering some of Japan’s most beautiful scenery, Shirakawa-ko isn’t all that famous. “Wait a second,” you might be saying, “isn’t that village in Gifu Prefecture with the thatched roofs one of the country’s most popular tourism spots?” But that’s Shirakawa-go, or “Shirakawa Village.” The place we’re talking about today is Shirakawa-ko, “Lake Shirakawa” in the town of Iide, Yamagata Prefecture.\n\nThe surrounding mountains are covered in snow throughout the winter, and when that snow finally melts in the spring, it flows into the lake, dramatically raising the water level from late March to late May. This partially floods an expansive grove of white willow trees, creating a submerged forest of mysteriously beautiful scenery in which the trees appear mirrored in the surface of the water.\n\nThe trees are almost entirely white until mid-April, but then their new spring leaves come in, creating an even more densely vegetated duplicated landscape.\n\nAs amazing as the submerged forest looks by day, though, it’s even more ethereally breathtaking at night.\n\nWith the willows illuminated as part of a special light-up event, they appear to be floating in space, since the rural location of the lake (which is about 40 minutes by car from Akayu Station on the Yamagata Shinkansen line) means there are hardly any other sources of light after sundown, except for the moon.\n\nThis year, the submerged forest will be illuminated from 6 to 9 p.m. on the nights of April 19 and 20, and from April 26 to May 11 (provided the weather isn’t rainy). There is an entrance fee of 1,000 yen (US$6.70) per person to the adjacent park, which goes to cover the costs of the illumination and contributes to a local nature conservation fund.\n\nThe park also has some rustic after-dark amenities during the event, and the illumination for the trees is provided entirely by battery-operated sources, so there won’t be any noisy gas-powered generators spoiling the tranquil mood.\n\n▼ Lake Shirakawa submerged forest location\n\nAs for what else there is to see in Iide, the local tourism office’s promotional video makes it look like exactly the sort of place that sparks daydreams of quitting your office job and moving to the Japanese countryside to start living the slow life.\n\nBut even if you spend only one night in Iide to see its submerged forest, odds are it’s a night you’ll never forget.\n\nRelated: Lake Shirakawa submerged forest tourism information website\n\nSource, images: PR Times\n\n● Want to hear about SoraNews24’s latest articles as soon as they’re published? Follow us on Facebook and Twitter!"}
{"topic": "Articles", "ss": "NewsApiFeeder", "ts": "2025-04-13T09:31:56Z", "url": "https://livefromalounge.com/on-april-15-delhi-airport-terminal-2-shuts-down-and-all-flights-move-to-terminal-1/", "publishedAt": "2025-04-13T09:31:56Z", "content": "Delhi’s Indira Gandhi International Airport, the largest airport in India, will close Terminal 2 for operations on April 15, 2025. All flights will then transition to Terminal 1.\r\nDelhi Airport Termi… [+3335 chars]", "title": "On April 15, Delhi Airport Terminal 2 shuts down and all flights move to Terminal 1", "fullContent": "Delhi’s Indira Gandhi International Airport, the largest airport in India, will close Terminal 2 for operations on April 15, 2025. All flights will then transition to Terminal 1.\n\nDelhi Airport Terminal 2 to shut down on April 15, 2025\n\nTerminal 1 was fully redone and made with a serviceable capacity of 40 million passengers annually. Now, Delhi Airport is consolidating its operations into T1 and T3. Terminal 2 will get a makeover, just like Terminal 1 did, but it is unclear if when it reopens, it will still be called Terminal 2 or Terminal 4, as the Delhi Airport Masterplan referred to it.\n\nThe extensive renovations will see the introduction of self-servicedling systems, and self-service check-in. The purpose of use is also unclear: will it be mixed use for domestic and international, or just fully domestic or fully international, and so on? baggage kiosks, new baggage han\n\n#2DaysToGo\n\nThe countdown is getting exciting! In just 2 days, experience a smarter, more comfortable journey at Delhi Airport’s upgraded Terminal 1.\n\nGet ready for smoother travel, better connectivity, and world-class facilities — all under one roof.#Terminal1 #DELAirport pic.twitter.com/DZ8ZYmSZw9 — Delhi Airport (@DelhiAirport) April 13, 2025\n\nAirlines to transition to Terminal 1 on April 15\n\nIndiGo will move 122 flights from Terminal 2 to Terminal 1. They have established a web page to announce which flights will transition from T2 to T1. It is best to check the time of your flight if it arrives or departs into T2 as well.\n\n#6ETravelAdvisory: From April 15, 2025, all #DelhiT2 flights will shift to #DelhiT1 due to maintenance. Expect possible schedule changes. Check terminal info https://t.co/Cp5tVZLarB and flight status https://t.co/TQCzzykjgA before heading to the airport. pic.twitter.com/KckE5IN4uG — IndiGo (@IndiGo6E) April 13, 2025\n\nSimilarly, Akasa will move from Terminal 2 to Terminal 1 as well. Details are here.\n\n#TravelUpdate: Starting 15 Apr 2025, all our flights to and from Delhi will operate from Terminal 1 (also known as 1D) of IGI Airport, Delhi. To ensure a seamless travel experience, we request you to plan for additional time to reach the airport well in time for your flight. Our… — Akasa Air (@AkasaAir) April 7, 2025\n\nThese are the two primary users of Terminal 2.\n\nBottomline\n\nTerminal 2 will be shut down at Delhi Airport on April 15, 2025, as of midnight. This means all flights currently operating from Terminal 2 will be transitioned out to Terminal 1, which will now operate at full capacity from that date on. Check with your airline to see if you are impacted.\n\nWhat do you make of this move at Delhi Airport?\n\nLiked our articles and our efforts? Please pay an amount you are comfortable with; an amount you believe is the fair price for the content you have consumed. Please enter an amount in the box below and click on the button to pay; you can use Netbanking, Debit/Credit Cards, UPI, QR codes, or any Wallet to pay. Every contribution helps cover the cost of the content generated for your benefit.\n\n(Important: to receive confirmation and details of your transaction, please enter a valid email address in the pop-up form that will appear after you click the ‘Pay Now’ button. For international transactions, use Paypal to process the transaction.)\n\nWe are not putting our articles behind any paywall where you are asked to pay before you r