with net income reaching CNY 1.09 billion. Despite a dividend yield of 3.22%, placing it in the top quartile of CN market payers, its high cash payout ratio (93.2%) raises concerns about sustainability. The dividend is covered by earnings but not free cash flows, and past payments have been volatile and unreliable, with significant annual drops over the last decade.\n\nSHSE:600598 Dividend History as at Apr 2025\n\nSimply Wall St Dividend Rating: ★★★★☆☆\n\nOverview: Warabeya Nichiyo Holdings Co., Ltd. operates in the manufacture and sale of food products for convenience stores both in Japan and internationally, with a market capitalization of ¥41.77 billion.\n\nOperations: Warabeya Nichiyo Holdings Co., Ltd. generates revenue through the production and distribution of food products specifically designed for convenience stores in both domestic and international markets.\n\nDividend Yield: 3.8%\n\nWarabeya Nichiyo Holdings offers a stable dividend history over the past decade, with payments consistently growing. However, the 3.76% yield is below top-tier levels in Japan and not well-supported by free cash flows or profits, despite a reasonable payout ratio of 58.7%. Recent challenges include delays in its U.S. expansion plans due to construction setbacks, potentially impacting future financial stability and dividend sustainability. The stock trades at good value relative to peers and industry standards."}
{"topic": "Articles", "ss": "NewsApiFeeder", "ts": "2025-04-13T06:02:58Z", "url": "https://finance.yahoo.com/news/wake-akzo-nobel-n-v-060258555.html", "publishedAt": "2025-04-13T06:02:58Z", "content": "<ul><li>Given the large stake in the stock by institutions, Akzo Nobel's stock price might be vulnerable to their trading decisions\r\n</li><li>The top 25 shareholders own 49% of the company\r\n</li><li>… [+5619 chars]", "title": "In the wake of Akzo Nobel N.V.'s (AMS:AKZA) latest €886m market cap drop, institutional owners may be forced to take severe actions", "fullContent": "Since institutional investors own more than half the issued stock, the board will likely have to pay attention to their preferences. Hedge funds don't have many shares in Akzo Nobel. Looking at our data, we can see that the largest shareholder is Dodge & Cox with 10% of shares outstanding. In comparison, the second and third largest shareholders hold about 5.4% and 5.0% of the stock.\n\nAkzo Nobel already has institutions on the share registry. Indeed, they own a respectable stake in the company. This can indicate that the company has a certain degree of credibility in the investment community. However, it is best to be wary of relying on the supposed validation that comes with institutional investors. They too, get it wrong sometimes. If multiple institutions change their view on a stock at the same time, you could see the share price drop fast. It's therefore worth looking at Akzo Nobel's earnings history below. Of course, the future is what really matters.\n\nInstitutions typically measure themselves against a benchmark when reporting to their own investors, so they often become more enthusiastic about a stock once it's included in a major index. We would expect most companies to have some institutions on the register, especially if they are growing.\n\nAnd institutional investors endured the highest losses after the company's share price fell by 9.5% last week. Needless to say, the recent loss which further adds to the one-year loss to shareholders of 22% might not go down well especially with this category of shareholders. Also referred to as \"smart money\", institutions have a lot of sway over how a stock's price moves. Hence, if weakness in Akzo Nobel's share price continues, institutional investors may feel compelled to sell the stock, which might not be ideal for individual investors.\n\nEvery investor in Akzo Nobel N.V. ( AMS:AKZA ) should be aware of the most powerful shareholder groups. We can see that institutions own the lion's share in the company with 55% ownership. Put another way, the group faces the maximum upside potential (or downside risk).\n\nGiven the large stake in the stock by institutions, Akzo Nobel's stock price might be vulnerable to their trading decisions\n\nStory Continues\n\nOur studies suggest that the top 25 shareholders collectively control less than half of the company's shares, meaning that the company's shares are widely disseminated and there is no dominant shareholder.\n\nResearching institutional ownership is a good way to gauge and filter a stock's expected performance. The same can be achieved by studying analyst sentiments. There are a reasonable number of analysts covering the stock, so it might be useful to find out their aggregate view on the future.\n\nInsider Ownership Of Akzo Nobel\n\nWhile the precise definition of an insider can be subjective, almost everyone considers board members to be insiders. Management ultimately answers to the board. However, it is not uncommon for managers to be executive board members, especially if they are a founder or the CEO.\n\nI generally consider insider ownership to be a good thing. However, on some occasions it makes it more difficult for other shareholders to hold the board accountable for decisions.\n\nOur most recent data indicates that insiders own less than 1% of Akzo Nobel N.V.. Being so large, we would not expect insiders to own a large proportion of the stock. Collectively, they own €3.2m of stock. Arguably recent buying and selling is just as important to consider. You can click here to see if insiders have been buying or selling.\n\nGeneral Public Ownership\n\nWith a 45% ownership, the general public, mostly comprising of individual investors, have some degree of sway over Akzo Nobel. While this size of ownership may not be enough to sway a policy decision in their favour, they can still make a collective impact on company policies.\n\nNext Steps:\n\nIt's always worth thinking about the different groups who own shares in a company. But to understand Akzo Nobel better, we need to consider many other factors. For example, we've discovered 2 warning signs for Akzo Nobel (1 can't be ignored!) that you should be aware of before investing here.\n\nBut ultimately it is the future, not the past, that will determine how well the owners of this business will do. Therefore we think it advisable to take a look at this free report showing whether analysts are predicting a brighter future .\n\nNB: Figures in this article are calculated using data from the last twelve months, which refer to the 12-month period ending on the last date of the month the financial statement is dated. This may not be consistent with full year annual report figures.\n\nHave feedback on this article? Concerned about the content? Get in touch with us directly. Alternatively, email editorial-team (at) simplywallst.com.\n\n\n\nThis article by Simply Wall St is general in nature. We provide commentary based on historical data and analyst forecasts only using an unbiased methodology and our articles are not intended to be financial advice. It does not constitute a recommendation to buy or sell any stock, and does not take account of your objectives, or your financial situation. We aim to bring you long-term focused analysis driven by fundamental data. Note that our analysis may not factor in the latest price-sensitive company announcements or qualitative material. Simply Wall St has no position in any stocks mentioned."}
{"topic": "Articles", "ss": "NewsApiFeeder", "ts": "2025-04-13T07:33:48Z", "url": "https://finance.yahoo.com/news/m-winkworth-plc-lon-wink-073348072.html", "publishedAt": "2025-04-13T07:33:48Z", "content": "Some investors rely on dividends for growing their wealth, and if you're one of those dividend sleuths, you might be intrigued to know that M Winkworth PLC (LON:WINK) is about to go ex-dividend in ju… [+4141 chars]", "title": "M Winkworth PLC (LON:WINK) Passed Our Checks, And It's About To Pay A UK£0.033 Dividend", "fullContent": "Some investors rely on dividends for growing their wealth, and if you're one of those dividend sleuths, you might be intrigued to know that M Winkworth PLC (LON:WINK) is about to go ex-dividend in just 3 days. The ex-dividend date generally occurs two days before the record date, which is the day on which shareholders need to be on the company's books in order to receive a dividend. The ex-dividend date is important because any transaction on a stock needs to have been settled before the record date in order to be eligible for a dividend. Meaning, you will need to purchase M Winkworth's shares before the 17th of April to receive the dividend, which will be paid on the 15th of May.\n\nThe company's next dividend payment will be UK£0.033 per share, on the back of last year when the company paid a total of UK£0.12 to shareholders. Looking at the last 12 months of distributions, M Winkworth has a trailing yield of approximately 6.5% on its current stock price of UK£2.02. We love seeing companies pay a dividend, but it's also important to be sure that laying the golden eggs isn't going to kill our golden goose! So we need to investigate whether M Winkworth can afford its dividend, and if the dividend could grow.\n\nTrump has pledged to \"unleash\" American oil and gas and these 15 US stocks have developments that are poised to benefit.\n\nDividends are usually paid out of company profits, so if a company pays out more than it earned then its dividend is usually at greater risk of being cut. It paid out 82% of its earnings as dividends last year, which is not unreasonable, but limits reinvestment in the business and leaves the dividend vulnerable to a business downturn. We'd be concerned if earnings began to decline.\n\nView our latest analysis for M Winkworth\n\nClick here to see how much of its profit M Winkworth paid out over the last 12 months.\n\nAIM:WINK Historic Dividend April 13th 2025\n\nHave Earnings And Dividends Been Growing?\n\nStocks in companies that generate sustainable earnings growth often make the best dividend prospects, as it is easier to lift the dividend when earnings are rising. If earnings fall far enough, the company could be forced to cut its dividend. With that in mind, we're encouraged by the steady growth at M Winkworth, with earnings per share up 9.6% on average over the last five years.\n\nMany investors will assess a company's dividend performance by evaluating how much the dividend payments have changed over time. Since the start of our data, 10 years ago, M Winkworth has lifted its dividend by approximately 9.3% a year on average. It's encouraging to see the company lifting dividends while earnings are growing, suggesting at least some corporate interest in rewarding shareholders."}
{"topic": "Articles", "ss": "NewsApiFeeder", "ts": "2025-04-13T00:18:48Z", "url": "https://finance.yahoo.com/news/petronas-dagangan-berhads-klse-petdag-001848432.html", "publishedAt": "2025-04-13T00:18:48Z", "content": "Most readers would already be aware that PETRONAS Dagangan Berhad's (KLSE:PETDAG) stock increased significantly by 11% over the past month. Since the market usually pay for a companys long-term funda… [+4624 chars]", "title": "PETRONAS Dagangan Berhad's (KLSE:PETDAG) Stock Is Going Strong: Is the Market Following Fundamentals?", "fullContent": "Most readers would already be aware that PETRONAS Dagangan Berhad's (KLSE:PETDAG) stock increased significantly by 11% over the past month. Since the market usually pay for a company’s long-term fundamentals, we decided to study the company’s key performance indicators to see if they could be influencing the market. Particularly, we will be paying attention to PETRONAS Dagangan Berhad's ROE today.\n\nROE or return on equity is a useful tool to assess how effectively a company can generate returns on the investment it received from its shareholders. In short, ROE shows the profit each dollar generates with respect to its shareholder investments.\n\nTrump has pledged to \"unleash\" American oil and gas and these 15 US stocks have developments that are poised to benefit.\n\nHow Is ROE Calculated?\n\nROE can be calculated by using the formula:\n\nReturn on Equity = Net Profit (from continuing operations) ÷ Shareholders' Equity\n\nSo, based on the above formula, the ROE for PETRONAS Dagangan Berhad is:\n\n18% = RM1.1b ÷ RM6.1b (Based on the trailing twelve months to December 2024).\n\nThe 'return' is the profit over the last twelve months. Another way to think of that is that for every MYR1 worth of equity, the company was able to earn MYR0.18 in profit.\n\nCheck out our latest analysis for PETRONAS Dagangan Berhad\n\nWhat Has ROE Got To Do With Earnings Growth?\n\nThus far, we have learned that ROE measures how efficiently a company is generating its profits. Based on how much of its profits the company chooses to reinvest or \"retain\", we are then able to evaluate a company's future ability to generate profits. Generally speaking, other things being equal, firms with a high return on equity and profit retention, have a higher growth rate than firms that don’t share these attributes.\n\nA Side By Side comparison of PETRONAS Dagangan Berhad's Earnings Growth And 18% ROE\n\nAt first glance, PETRONAS Dagangan Berhad seems to have a decent ROE. On comparing with the average industry ROE of 8.8% the company's ROE looks pretty remarkable. This probably laid the ground for PETRONAS Dagangan Berhad's moderate 19% net income growth seen over the past five years.\n\nAs a next step, we compared PETRONAS Dagangan Berhad's net income growth with the industry and found that the company has a similar growth figure when compared with the industry average growth rate of 19% in the same period.\n\nKLSE:PETDAG Past Earnings Growth April 13th 2025\n\nEarnings growth is a huge factor in stock valuation. The investor should try to establish if the expected growth or decline in earnings, whichever the case may be, is priced in. By doing so, they will have an idea if the stock is headed into clear blue waters or if swampy waters await. Has the market priced in the future outlook for PETDAG? You can find out in our latest intrinsic value infographic research report."}
{"topic": "Articles", "ss": "NewsApiFeeder", "ts": "2025-04-13T00:27:12Z", "url": "https://finance.yahoo.com/news/pleasing-signs-number-insiders-buy-002712360.html", "publishedAt": "2025-04-13T00:27:12Z", "content": "When a single insider purchases stock, it is typically not a major deal. However, when multiple insiders purchase stock, like in Jupiter Mines Limited's (ASX:JMS) instance, it's good news for shareho… [+4088 chars]", "title": "Pleasing Signs As A Number Of Insiders Buy Jupiter Mines Stock", "fullContent": "When a single insider purchases stock, it is typically not a major deal. However, when multiple insiders purchase stock, like in Jupiter Mines Limited's (ASX:JMS) instance, it's good news for shareholders.\n\nWhile we would never suggest that investors should base their decisions solely on what the directors of a company have been doing, logic dictates you should pay some attention to whether insiders are buying or selling shares.\n\nAI is about to change healthcare. These 20 stocks are working on everything from early diagnostics to drug discovery. The best part - they are all under $10bn in marketcap - there is still time to get in early.\n\nJupiter Mines Insider Transactions Over The Last Year\n\nOver the last year, we can see that the biggest insider purchase was by insider Peter North for AU$88k worth of shares, at about AU$0.17 per share. That means that even when the share price was higher than AU$0.15 (the recent price), an insider wanted to purchase shares. It's very possible they regret the purchase, but it's more likely they are bullish about the company. In our view, the price an insider pays for shares is very important. Generally speaking, it catches our eye when insiders have purchased shares at above current prices, as it suggests they believed the shares were worth buying, even at a higher price.\n\nJupiter Mines insiders may have bought shares in the last year, but they didn't sell any. You can see a visual depiction of insider transactions (by companies and individuals) over the last 12 months, below. If you want to know exactly who sold, for how much, and when, simply click on the graph below!\n\nSee our latest analysis for Jupiter Mines\n\nASX:JMS Insider Trading Volume April 13th 2025\n\nThere are always plenty of stocks that insiders are buying. If investing in lesser known companies is your style, you could take a look at this free list of companies. (Hint: insiders have been buying them).\n\nDoes Jupiter Mines Boast High Insider Ownership?\n\nLooking at the total insider shareholdings in a company can help to inform your view of whether they are well aligned with common shareholders. Usually, the higher the insider ownership, the more likely it is that insiders will be incentivised to build the company for the long term. From looking at our data, insiders own AU$6.2m worth of Jupiter Mines stock, about 2.1% of the company. However, it's possible that insiders might have an indirect interest through a more complex structure. We consider this fairly low insider ownership.\n\nSo What Do The Jupiter Mines Insider Transactions Indicate?\n\nThere haven't been any insider transactions in the last three months -- that doesn't mean much. However, our analysis of transactions over the last year is heartening. We'd like to see bigger individual holdings. However, we don't see anything to make us think Jupiter Mines insiders are doubting the company. While it's good to be aware of what's going on with the insider's ownership and transactions, we make sure to also consider what risks are facing a stock before making any investment decision. To that end, you should learn about the 3 warning signs we've spotted with Jupiter Mines (including 1 which is a bit concerning) ."}
{"topic": "Articles", "ss": "NewsApiFeeder", "ts": "2025-04-13T07:30:36Z", "url": "https://www.decanter.com/premium/vermentino-2023-tuscany-vs-sardinia-panel-tasting-results-554261/", "publishedAt": "2025-04-13T07:30:36Z", "content": "Jason Millar, Michael Garner, and Vincenzo Arnese tasted 83 wines, with 18 Highly Recommended\r\nVermentino 2023: Panel tasting scores\r\n83 wines tasted\r\nExceptional 0\r\nOutstanding 1\r\nHighly recommended… [+11934 chars]", "title": "Vermentino 2023 Tuscany vs Sardinia: Panel tasting results", "fullContent": "Jason Millar, Michael Garner, and Vincenzo Arnese tasted 83 wines, with 18 Highly Recommended\n\nVermentino 2023: Panel tasting scores\n\n83 wines tasted\n\nExceptional 0\n\nOutstanding 1\n\nHighly recommended 18\n\nRecommended 55\n\nCommended 9\n\nEntry criteria: producers and UK agents were invited to submit their Vermentino wines from Sardinia or Tuscany, from the 2023 vintage only\n\nFashionable Vermentino has been making a name for itself in recent years. Native to Italy, the grape is synonymous with Sardinia, which boasts two-thirds of the country’s plantings, but this century has seen the island’s dominance challenged by the Tuscan coast’s ambitious and skilled winemakers.\n\nThis exciting panel tasting set out to discover whether it’s the Sardinians or the Tuscans who are currently making Italy’s most impressive Vermentino – and the results were fascinating.\n\nThe top-scoring Vermentino from the panel tasting are listed below\n\n{\"content\":\"\"}\n\nVermentino 2023 panel tasting results\n\nWines were tasted blind\n\n{} {\"wineId\":\"94199\",\"displayCase\":\"standard\",\"paywall\":true} {\"wineId\":\"94200\",\"displayCase\":\"standard\",\"paywall\":true} {\"wineId\":\"94201\",\"displayCase\":\"standard\",\"paywall\":true} {\"wineId\":\"94202\",\"displayCase\":\"standard\",\"paywall\":true} {\"wineId\":\"94203\",\"displayCase\":\"standard\",\"paywall\":true} {\"wineId\":\"94204\",\"displayCase\":\"standard\",\"paywall\":true} {\"wineId\":\"94205\",\"displayCase\":\"standard\",\"paywall\":true} {\"wineId\":\"94206\",\"displayCase\":\"standard\",\"paywall\":true} {\"wineId\":\"94207\",\"displayCase\":\"standard\",\"paywall\":true} {\"wineId\":\"94208\",\"displayCase\":\"standard\",\"paywall\":true} {\"wineId\":\"94209\",\"displayCase\":\"standard\",\"paywall\":true} {\"wineId\":\"94210\",\"displayCase\":\"standard\",\"paywall\":true} {\"wineId\":\"94211\",\"displayCase\":\"standard\",\"paywall\":true} {\"wineId\":\"94212\",\"displayCase\":\"standard\",\"paywall\":true} {\"wineId\":\"94213\",\"displayCase\":\"standard\",\"paywall\":true} {\"wineId\":\"94214\",\"displayCase\":\"standard\",\"paywall\":true} {\"wineId\":\"94215\",\"displayCase\":\"standard\",\"paywall\":true} {\"wineId\":\"94216\",\"displayCase\":\"standard\",\"paywall\":true} {\"wineId\":\"94217\",\"displayCase\":\"standard\",\"paywall\":true} {}\n\nThe judges\n\nJason Millar is a freelance wine writer, consultant, judge and communicator, with a focus on Italy and South Africa. He has a background in buying, importing and sales, and in 2016 was the top WSET Diploma graduate worldwide\n\nVincenzo Arnese is director of wine at Raffles London at the OWO. Born in Naples, he worked at top hotels in Italy, Switzerland and Australia, and later Alain Ducasse at The Dorchester. A DWWA judge, in 2022 he won the coveted title of Taittinger UK Sommelier of the Year\n\nMichael Garner is co-owner of Italian specialist Tria Wines and DWWA Regional Chair for Northern Italy. He is the author of Amarone and the Fine Wines of Verona (£35 Académie du Vin Library, 2017)\n\nRelated articles"}
{"topic": "Articles", "ss": "NewsApiFeeder", "ts": "2025-04-13T03:54:02Z", "url": "https://www.lewrockwell.com/lrc-blog/the-secret-history-of-western-education-the-scientific-destruction-of-minds-charlotte-iserbyt/", "publishedAt": "2025-04-13T03:54:02Z", "content": "https://www.lewrockwell.com/lrc-blog/the-secret-history-of-western-education-the-scientific-destruction-of-minds-charlotte-iserbyt/The late Charlotte Iserbyt was the consummate whistleblower! Iserbyt… [+2301 chars]", "title": "The Secret History of Western Education – The Scientific Destruction of Minds – Charlotte Iserbyt", "fullContent": "https://www.lewrockwell.com/lrc-blog/the-secret-history-of-western-education-the-scientific-destruction-of-minds-charlotte-iserbyt/\n\nThe late Charlotte Iserbyt was the consummate whistleblower! Iserbyt served as Senior Policy Advisor in the Office of Educational Research and Improvement (OERI), U.S. Department of Education, during the first Reagan Administration, where she first blew the whistle on a major technology initiative which would control curriculum in America’s classrooms.\n\nCharlotte T. Iserbyt, 91 of Dresden, passed away at her home on the afternoon of February 8, 2022. Born in New York on October 26, 1930, she was the daughter of Clifton and Charlotte (Thomson), and the wife of the late Jan Iserbyt.\n\nIserbyt’s father and grandfather were Yale University graduates and members of the Skull and Bones secret society.\n\nIserbyt was a former school board director in Camden, Maine and was co-founder and research analyst of Guardians of Education for Maine (GEM) from 1978 to 2000. She has also served in the American Red Cross on Guam and Japan during the Korean War, and in the United States Foreign Service in Belgium and in the Republic of South Africa.\n\nIserbyt was a speaker and writer, best known for her 1985 booklet Back to Basics Reform or OBE: Skinnerian International Curriculum and her 1989 pamphlet Soviets in the Classroom: America’s Latest Education Fad which covered the details of the U.S.-Soviet and Carnegie-Soviet Education Agreements which remain in effect to this day.\n\nA prolific writer, Ms. Iserbyt authored two books, The Deliberate Dumbing Down of America…A Chronological Paper Trail in 1999, which alleges that changes gradually brought into the American public education system work to eliminate the influences of a child’s parents and mold the child into a member of the proletariat in preparation for a socialist-collectivist world of the future. She also wrote three editions of Back to Basics Reform or…OBE*Skinnerian International Curriculum between 1985 and 2003 and Back to Basics Reform, which documents her experiences working in the U.S. Department of Education, where she was privy to past and future plans to restructure American education.\n\nMs. Iserbyt contributed numerous articles to professional journals and newspapers. She was a freelance writer and had articles published in Human Events, The Washington Times, The Bangor Daily News, and included in the record of Congressional hearings.\n\n11:54 pm on April 12, 2025\n\nThe Best of Charles Burris"}
{"topic": "Articles", "ss": "NewsApiFeeder", "ts": "2025-04-13T05:20:20Z", "url": "https://goodereader.com/blog/kindle/amazon-kindle-rewards-will-be-easier-to-redeem", "publishedAt": "2025-04-13T05:20:20Z", "content": "Amazon is making changes to the Kindle Rewards Beta program in the United States. They are making it easier to redeem e-book credits right on the product description page for print books and digital … [+1832 chars]", "title": "Amazon Kindle Rewards will be easier to redeem", "fullContent": "Amazon is making changes to the Kindle Rewards Beta program in the United States. They are making it easier to redeem e-book credits right on the product description page for print books and digital books. Right under the add to cart button is a box, that provides the total number of credits that are owned and simply check mark the box, before adding it to the cart to get a discount for the book.\n\nThe redemption process on the product description page does have its caveats. It has to be done on the Amazon website, which can be accessed on a computer, laptop, phone or tablet. It won’t work on the Kindle Shopping app, Kindle e-reader to any of the Kindle apps for Android or iOS.\n\nAmazon will discontinue the original process of redeeming points from the Kindle Rewards Beta page on May 11th, 2025. The change to Kindle Rewards is a welcome one, it simplifies the process, making it more intuitive to use credits to get discounts on books.\n\nWhat is Kindle Rewards?\n\nLots of people might not be familiar with Kindle Rewards. At its core, US customers earn credits when purchasing print books or e-books. Once 300 credits are attained, it provides a $3.00 discount that can be used on any title on the Amazon bookstore.\n\nCustomers earn 3 Kindle Points per dollar spent on Kindle books and 1 Kindle Point per dollar spent on print books. The amount of points is listed on the Amazon website, right underneath the price. Sometimes, Amazon offers double the points that they announce on social media. These often run for a few days or, in some rare cases, last one week. One of the downsides of the program, is that lots of books have to be purchased just to earn a few credits and Kindle Points expire after three months.\n\nMichael Kozlowski Michael Kozlowski is the editor-in-chief at Good e-Reader and has written about audiobooks and e-readers for the past fifteen years. Newspapers and websites such as the CBC, CNET, Engadget, Huffington Post and the New York Times have picked up his articles. He Lives in Vancouver, British Columbia, Canada."}
{"topic": "Articles", "ss": "NewsApiFeeder", "ts": "2025-04-13T22:55:49Z", "url": "https://ask.metafilter.com/385297/Where-are-the-ethical-hackers", "publishedAt": "2025-04-13T22:55:49Z", "content": "I feel like during the Occupy days Anonymous was out there doing (occasional) good hacking deeds and since then there's been some hack/leak type things I could name like the Panama Papers. But right … [+681 chars]", "title": "Where are the ethical hackers?", "fullContent": "I feel like during the Occupy days Anonymous was out there doing (occasional) good hacking deeds and since then there's been some hack/leak type things I could name like the Panama Papers . But right now where are the good guys hacking and cracking for reasons other than stealing Bitcoin and installing ransomware? Where's the spoofed cellphone that's not stealing a bank pin but instead dumping collusion texts between everyone's least favorite wanna-be autocrats and the current crop of man child techno-facists? Where's the bot net turned on the hedge fund assholes turning a non-profit hospital into a debt collecting machine? Or whatever! You know, I just feel like this world, right now, is ripe for this and I'm not hearing about it or it's not happening?Happy to hear more examples from the past, but I'm mostly curious about the right now -- groups, news articles, etc..."}
{"topic": "Articles", "ss": "NewsApiFeeder", "ts": "2025-04-13T14:00:10Z", "url": "https://www.geeky-gadgets.com/discover-the-iphone-17-series-design-battery-and-camera-upgrade/", "publishedAt": "2025-04-13T14:00:10Z", "content": "The iPhone 17 series introduces a host of innovations aimed at enhancing your experience in photography, content creation, and overall performance. From dual-camera recording to upgraded hardware and… [+5801 chars]", "title": "Discover the iPhone 17 Series: Design, Battery, and Camera Upgrade", "fullContent": "The iPhone 17 series introduces a host of innovations aimed at enhancing your experience in photography, content creation, and overall performance. From dual-camera recording to upgraded hardware and refined aesthetics, Apple continues its tradition of pushing the boundaries of mobile technology. While the Pro models feature exclusive advancements, the entire lineup reflects a commitment to delivering innovative capabilities that cater to a wide range of users. The video below from SaranByte gives us more details on what to expect from the iPhone 17 Series.\n\nDual-Camera Recording: Transforming Content Creation\n\nOne of the standout features of the iPhone 17 is its dual-camera recording capability, which allows simultaneous video capture from both the front and rear cameras. This feature is particularly appealing to content creators, allowing dynamic storytelling by seamlessly switching perspectives in real time. Whether you’re vlogging, conducting interviews, or creating cinematic content, this tool opens up new possibilities for creativity. Although this feature may be exclusive to the Pro models, it sets a new standard for mobile videography, rivaling similar offerings on premium Android devices and further solidifying Apple’s position as a leader in the industry.\n\nRedesigned Camera Module: A Fusion of Functionality and Style\n\nThe Pro models in the iPhone 17 series showcase a redesigned camera module that merges functionality with aesthetics. The larger camera bump accommodates advanced components, including a new telephoto lens, while the repositioning of elements such as the LiDAR scanner, microphone, and flash enhances usability. Apple has maintained its signature sleek design, making sure that the updated module aligns with its minimalist design philosophy. This balance between form and function not only improves the device’s visual appeal but also enhances its practicality for photography enthusiasts and everyday users alike.\n\nTelephoto Lens Upgrade: Elevating Mobile Photography\n\nPhotography enthusiasts will appreciate the significant improvements to the telephoto lens in the Pro models. The introduction of a 48 MP telephoto sensor, replacing the previous 12 MP lens, delivers sharper images, superior low-light performance, and enhanced portrait photography. For those who demand even more, the Pro Max model offers digital zoom capabilities of up to 30x or 40x, making it ideal for capturing distant subjects with remarkable clarity. These advancements cater to both casual users and professionals, making sure that the iPhone 17 remains a top choice for mobile photography.\n\nThermal Management: Optimized for Performance\n\nThe iPhone 17 Pro models introduce a vapor chamber heat sink, a feature designed to improve thermal performance during demanding tasks. Whether you’re gaming, editing videos, or using the camera for extended periods, this innovation ensures that your device stays cool and performs efficiently. By addressing heat dissipation more effectively, Apple not only enhances the device’s performance but also extends its longevity, making it a reliable choice for users who push their devices to the limit.\n\nMaterial and Design Refinements: Durable Elegance\n\nApple has made subtle yet impactful design changes across the iPhone 17 lineup. The Pro models may feature aluminum construction, offering brighter color options and a premium feel. Meanwhile, the iPhone 17 Air adopts a thinner profile with a single-lens camera bar and a glass back, striking a balance between aesthetics and functionality. These refinements ensure that the devices remain visually appealing while accommodating the latest technological advancements. The combination of durability and elegance reflects Apple’s commitment to delivering products that are both practical and stylish.\n\nBattery Life: Enhanced Endurance\n\nBattery performance sees meaningful improvements across the iPhone 17 series. The iPhone 17 Air incorporates high-density battery technology, maintaining impressive endurance despite its slim design. On the other hand, the Pro Max model includes a larger battery, slightly increasing the device’s thickness but delivering extended usage times. These enhancements cater to users who rely on their devices for productivity, entertainment, and communication throughout the day, making sure that the iPhone 17 can keep up with even the most demanding schedules.\n\nHardware Upgrades: Seamless and Efficient Performance\n\nThe iPhone 17 Pro models receive a notable RAM upgrade, increasing to 12 GB to support multitasking and future software demands. Base models retain 8 GB of RAM, making sure reliable performance for everyday tasks. These hardware improvements highlight Apple’s focus on delivering a smooth and efficient user experience across its product range. Whether you’re running resource-intensive applications or managing multiple tasks simultaneously, the iPhone 17 is designed to handle it all with ease.\n\nA Thoughtful Evolution of Mobile Technology\n\nThe iPhone 17 series represents a thoughtful evolution of Apple’s flagship lineup, balancing innovation with practicality. While the Pro models stand out with features like dual-camera recording, advanced telephoto lenses, and improved thermal management, the entire range benefits from enhanced design, battery technology, and hardware upgrades. Whether you’re a content creator, photography enthusiast, or power user, the iPhone 17 offers tools and capabilities that elevate your mobile experience, making sure that it remains a versatile and reliable companion in your daily life.\n\nDiscover other guides from our vast content that could be of interest on iPhone 17 dual-camera recording.\n\nSource & Image Credit: SaranByte\n\n\n\nLatest Geeky Gadgets Deals\n\nSome of our articles include affiliate links. If you buy something through one of these links, Geeky Gadgets may earn an affiliate commission. Learn about our Disclosure Policy"}
{"topic": "Articles", "ss": "NewsApiFeeder", "ts": "2025-04-13T13:00:32Z", "url": "https://www.geeky-gadgets.com/ios-18-4-hidden-features-revealed/", "publishedAt": "2025-04-13T13:00:32Z", "content": "Apple’s iOS 18.4 brings a host of subtle yet impactful updates aimed at refining the way you use your iPhone. These enhancements focus on improving usability, expanding personalization, and strengthe… [+5121 chars]", "title": "Secret iPhone Tricks! iOS 18.4 Hidden Features Revealed", "fullContent": "Apple’s iOS 18.4 brings a host of subtle yet impactful updates aimed at refining the way you use your iPhone. These enhancements focus on improving usability, expanding personalization, and strengthening privacy. Whether you’re a casual user or a tech enthusiast, understanding these features can help you unlock the full potential of your device. Below is a detailed exploration of the most noteworthy updates and how they can enhance your daily experience in a new video from HotshotTek.\n\nEnhanced Control Center: Music at Your Fingertips\n\nThe Control Center in iOS 18.4 has been upgraded to offer a more intuitive and versatile experience. One of the standout additions is the integration of ambient music playlists, which are categorized into modes such as:\n\nWell-being\n\nProductivity\n\nChill\n\nSleep\n\nEven if you’re not an Apple Music subscriber, you can now link your personal playlists directly to the Control Center. This ensures that your favorite tracks are always accessible, no matter which music platform you prefer. Whether you’re preparing for a productive day or winding down in the evening, this feature allows you to set the perfect mood effortlessly. The improved accessibility and customization make the Control Center a more powerful tool for managing your audio experience.\n\nStreamlined Email Management\n\nThe Mail app has received subtle yet impactful updates to improve how you manage your inbox. A new “delete or move message” action allows you to customize what happens after you delete an email. This feature simplifies navigation within your inbox, allowing you to process messages more efficiently.\n\nFor users who handle a high volume of emails daily, this enhancement can save valuable time by reducing unnecessary steps. Whether you’re organizing work correspondence or clearing out spam, the streamlined functionality ensures a smoother and more productive email experience.\n\nVoice Memo Privacy: Greater Control Over Your Data\n\nPrivacy remains a cornerstone of iOS 18.4, with significant improvements to the Voice Memos app. Users now have the ability to reset the identifier used for app usage statistics reporting, giving you more control over how your data is shared. This feature ensures that your privacy preferences are respected and provides greater transparency regarding data usage.\n\nFor those who prioritize safeguarding personal information, this update represents a meaningful step forward. It enables you to make informed decisions about your data while continuing to enjoy the convenience of the Voice Memos app.\n\nShortcuts App: Smarter and More Efficient\n\nThe Shortcuts app has been enhanced to streamline your daily tasks and improve productivity. Two key updates stand out:\n\nA new shortcut allows you to quickly switch between Safari search engines, giving you faster access to the information you need.\n\nYou can now create a shortcut to open recent conversations directly from the side button or the app itself, simplifying communication.\n\nThese updates are designed to save time and reduce friction in your workflow. Whether you’re conducting research or staying connected with friends and colleagues, the improved Shortcuts app makes it easier to accomplish tasks with minimal effort.\n\nSiri and Apple Intelligence: Smarter and More Flexible\n\nSiri and Apple Intelligence have been fine-tuned to offer greater flexibility and smarter suggestions. A notable update allows you to disable Apple Intelligence activation via the side button, giving you more control over when and how these features are used.\n\nThis refinement ensures that Siri works on your terms, adapting to your preferences and needs. Whether you’re using Siri for quick commands or relying on Apple Intelligence for personalized suggestions, these updates make the experience more intuitive and user-friendly.\n\nPhotos App: Tailored to Your Preferences\n\nThe Photos app now offers enhanced customization options, allowing you to rearrange utility sections such as screenshots and receipts. This feature makes it easier to organize your photo library in a way that aligns with your preferences.\n\nBy tailoring the layout to suit your needs, you can navigate your collection more efficiently while keeping it visually appealing. Whether you’re managing personal memories or work-related images, the improved organization tools make the Photos app more practical and enjoyable to use.\n\nUnlock the Potential of iOS 18.4\n\niOS 18.4 introduces a range of hidden features designed to enhance customization, privacy, and usability across your iPhone. From organizing your photos and managing emails to interacting with Siri and streamlining daily tasks, these updates are crafted to make your device more intuitive and personalized. By exploring these features, you can enjoy a more seamless and efficient user experience tailored to your unique needs and preferences.\n\nAdvance your knowledge of iOS 18.4 hidden features by reading more of our detailed content.\n\nSource & Image Credit: HotshotTek\n\n\n\nLatest Geeky Gadgets Deals\n\nSome of our articles include affiliate links. If you buy something through one of these links, Geeky Gadgets may earn an affiliate commission. Learn about our Disclosure Policy"}
{"topic": "Articles", "ss": "NewsApiFeeder", "ts": "2025-04-13T12:03:59Z", "url": "https://www.geeky-gadgets.com/linkedin-leads-for-free-2025/", "publishedAt": "2025-04-13T12:03:59Z", "content": "Generating leads on LinkedIn can often seem like a costly and time-intensive process, especially when relying on paid tools. However, by using free resources and automation workflows, you can streaml… [+6212 chars]", "title": "Generate High-Quality LinkedIn Leads for Free with n8n Automations", "fullContent": "Generating leads on LinkedIn can often seem like a costly and time-intensive process, especially when relying on paid tools. However, by using free resources and automation workflows, you can streamline the process and identify high-quality prospects efficiently. In this guide, AI Agents A-Z walk you through a step-by-step process to streamline your lead generation efforts using tools like n8n, job boards, and LinkedIn data scraping. By combining automation with strategic data collection, you’ll uncover high-quality prospects while saving time and resources. Whether you’re a sales professional, a business owner, or someone looking to scale your outreach, this method offers a practical, ethical, and cost-effective solution to supercharge your prospecting efforts.\n\nAutomated LinkedIn Leads with n8n\n\nTL;DR Key Takeaways : Use job boards like Remotive to identify companies with hiring needs that align with your offerings, forming the foundation of your lead generation workflow.\n\nExtract actionable data from LinkedIn using tools like the Google Custom Search API to gather comprehensive company information, including descriptions, employee counts, and updates.\n\nAggregate and summarize raw data into structured insights using tools like spreadsheets, databases, and LLMs (e.g., OpenAI) to enhance targeting and outreach effectiveness.\n\nCustomize the output for actionable use by integrating data into CRMs, generating personalized LinkedIn messages, or sharing insights with sales teams for follow-up.\n\nAutomate responsibly by incorporating delays to mimic human behavior, adhering to ethical scraping practices, and complying with LinkedIn’s terms of service to avoid detection and maintain trust.\n\n1: Use Job Boards to Identify Sales Opportunities\n\nJob boards are a valuable resource for uncovering sales opportunities. Job postings often indicate hiring budgets, growth initiatives, and potential interest in your product or service. Platforms like Remotive, which provide industry-specific RSS feeds, are particularly effective for gathering relevant data.\n\nFocus on job postings that align with your offerings. For example, if you provide HR software, target companies hiring HR managers or recruiters.\n\nExtract critical details such as job titles, company names, and locations. These details form the foundation of your lead generation workflow.\n\nBy targeting companies actively hiring, you can identify organizations with potential needs that your solution can address. This approach ensures your efforts are directed toward prospects with a higher likelihood of engagement.\n\n2: Extract Actionable Data from LinkedIn\n\nOnce you’ve identified relevant job postings, the next step is to extract actionable data from LinkedIn. Tools like the Google Custom Search API can assist in locating LinkedIn company pages based on the company names collected from job boards.\n\nUse the API to perform precise searches, narrowing down results to the most relevant LinkedIn profiles.\n\nExtract key company information, such as descriptions, employee counts, locations, and recent updates.\n\nIncorporate conditional logic into your workflow to handle incomplete data. For instance, if a company page lacks employee information, the workflow can skip to the next available data point without interruption.\n\nThis step ensures you gather comprehensive and relevant information about your prospects, allowing more informed decision-making during outreach.\n\nLinkedIn leads with n8n without paying\n\nAdvance your skills in LinkedIn lead generation by reading more of our detailed content.\n\n3: Aggregate and Summarize the Data\n\nRaw data becomes valuable only when it is structured and easy to analyze. Aggregating and summarizing the extracted data allows you to transform it into actionable insights.\n\nUse data aggregation tools to compile information into spreadsheets or databases, creating a centralized repository of prospects.\n\nEnhance the data with a Large Language Model (LLM) like OpenAI to generate summaries. These summaries can highlight why a company is a strong prospect, based on factors such as hiring trends or recent updates.\n\nFor example, if a company recently announced plans to expand into new markets, the LLM can summarize this as an indicator of potential interest in solutions that support scaling operations. This process converts raw data into meaningful insights, making your outreach efforts more focused and effective.\n\n4: Tailor the Output for Actionable Use\n\nThe final output of your workflow should be customized to meet your specific needs. Whether you’re sharing data with a sales team or integrating it into a CRM, the goal is to make the information actionable and practical.\n\nSend summarized data via email to stakeholders, such as sales teams or business development managers, for immediate follow-up.\n\nIntegrate the data into a CRM system to ensure it’s readily available for future outreach and tracking.\n\nFor LinkedIn outreach, generate personalized connection requests or messages. Reference a company’s recent achievements or growth plans to make your outreach more compelling and relevant.\n\nTailoring the output ensures that your efforts translate into meaningful engagement with prospects, increasing the likelihood of successful conversions.\n\nStep 5: Automate Responsibly and Ethically\n\nAutomation is essential for scaling this process, but it must be implemented responsibly to avoid detection and maintain ethical standards.\n\nIncorporate loops with wait times into your workflow to mimic human behavior. For example, add delays between scraping actions to reduce the risk of triggering LinkedIn’s bot detection mechanisms.\n\nAdhere to ethical scraping practices by complying with LinkedIn’s terms of service. Avoid collecting sensitive or private data, and prioritize transparency and respect for data privacy.\n\nBy automating responsibly, you can scale your lead generation efforts without compromising trust or facing legal complications. Ethical practices not only protect your business but also foster long-term relationships with prospects.\n\nA Practical and Scalable Approach to LinkedIn Lead Generation\n\nThis workflow provides a practical, scalable, and cost-effective method for generating LinkedIn leads without relying on paid tools. By combining job board scraping, LinkedIn data extraction, and automation tools like n8n, you can create a robust lead generation system. The integration of data aggregation and summarization further enhances the quality of your outputs, allowing more targeted and impactful outreach.\n\nWith careful attention to ethical practices and bot detection avoidance, this approach enables businesses to expand their prospecting efforts efficiently. Whether you’re a sales professional or a business development manager, this workflow equips you with the tools and strategies needed to identify and engage high-quality prospects on LinkedIn effectively.\n\nMedia Credit: AI Agents A-Z\n\n\n\nLatest Geeky Gadgets Deals\n\nSome of our articles include affiliate links. If you buy something through one of these links, Geeky Gadgets may earn an affiliate commission. Learn about our Disclosure Policy"}
